data.description: Unique Mountain Home on 20 Acres in Florissant, Colorado nestled in the pines and aspens of the Colorado Central Mountains is ready to become your new home. Take the 360 tour to get a true idea of this special property, then plan a trip to see the property in person. Nestled in the mountains behind Pikes Peak, come escape the hustle and bustle of the city on this amazing 20 acre-mountain retreat where you can enjoy the peace and quiet of the Colorado mountains. Imagine waking up to the awe-inspiring beauty of mountains, in a home that seamlessly blends indoor and outdoor living.  Change your entire life by telecommuting from the Colorado mountains and enjoy the mountain life 365 days a year. You will appreciate the location - just five minutes to a major paved road - County Road 112, plus a short 45-minute drive to Woodland Park The Central Colorado Mountains include several communities west of Colorado Springs including Florissant, Divide, Cripple Creek, Victor and Lake George. Florissant is surrounded by thousands of acres of the Pike National Forest to explore and enjoy. Residents have endless options for outdoor activities such as: boating on Eleven Mile and Spinney Reservoirs, fishing in the Gold Medal Waters of the Dream Stream, discovering Guffey's Paradise Cove, biking & hiking in Mueller State Park, exploring the Florissant Fossil Beds  and the mining towns of  Cripple Creek,  and Victor. In addition, we are only a 90 miles drive to World Class skiing in Breckenridge or Monarch.   The property is approximately a 70-minute drive from downtown Colorado Springs, offering easy air transportation from the Colorado Springs Airport.
